We do not believe, based on a review of your request, that your case meets one or more of the expedite criteria and otherwise merits expedited processing. We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director.  Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria.  If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director.  Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria.  If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

We do not believe, based on a review of your request, that your case meets one or more of the expedite criteria and otherwise merits expedited processing. We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director.  Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria. checking USCIS for Reciept: WAC2190042104
On March 8, 2021, we denied your request for expedited processing of your I-129F, Petition for Alien Fiancé(e), Receipt Number WAC2190042104.  We do not believe, based on a review of your request, that your case meets one or more of the expedite criteria and otherwise merits expedited processing. We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director.  Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria.  If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

On August 4, 2021, we denied your request for expedited processing of your I-765, Application for Employment Authorization, Receipt Number WAC2190042242.  We do not believe, based on a review of your request, that your case meets one or more of the expedite criteria and otherwise merits expedited processing. We review all expedite requests on a case-by-case basis, and we grant them at the discretion of the director.  Information regarding the USCIS expedite policy, including the expedite criteria, is available at www.uscis.gov/forms/expedite-criteria. checking USCIS for Reciept: WAC2190043031

We will hold your document for 180 days or until December 19, 2021. If you do not submit an online request or call us by December 19, 2021, we will destroy your document and you will need to file a new Form I-539, Application To Extend/Change Nonimmigrant Status, with fee.
